title: Safeway’s owner Albertsons postpones IPO, signaling trouble ahead
text:
Photo: Paul Chinn, The Chronicle The Safeway store at College and Claremont avenues is seen in Oakland, Calif. on Wednesday, Oct. 14, 2015. Cerberus Capital Management, which just completed a merger between its Safeway and Albertson's grocery stores, plans on taking the supermarket chains public again. The Safeway store at College and Claremont avenues is seen in...
Albertsons’ plan to go public less than a year after it bought Safeway, creating the nation’s second-largest supermarket chain, appears to be on hold indefinitely.
